	   <tr><td colspan=2>I started a vah shir shaman when Luclin first came out.&nbsp;&nbsp;He worked his way up to level 19 and has been sitting around collection dust every since.  Im thinking about dusting him off and trying to play him again.  My question, one of them anyway, is what should I look for in the way of equipment?  With my druid all I have to worry about is wisdom, as hes primarily a caster.  With my ranger Im interested in armor class, as hes primarily a warrior.  But the shaman class seems to be split down the middle between a caster and a warrior.  I have a hard enough time trying to equip my characters when I only have to worry about one stat.  How in the world do I get equipment that will give him both high wisdom and high AC?  I have a bit of money saved up, but Im far from rich.  I cant afford to pay 2 or 3k for every piece of equipment I buy.  My poor kitty would be running around mostly necked if I did.  *grin*  So higher end items are out for the moment.  Is there any mid level equipment I can shop for that will get me both stats or do I have to make a choice on one stat or the other?<br><br>Thanks,<br><br>&nbsp;<br><b>Namir Shadowstalker</b><br>Wood Elf Ranger, 49th Season<br><b>Calabar Silverthorn</b><br>Wood Elf Druid, 50th Season<br><b>Moonshadows</b><br><b>Seventh Hammer</b></td></tr>
