	   <tr><td colspan=2>Yes, all vah shir classes are agnostic, unless something has changed recently that Im not aware of.&nbsp;&nbsp;For a shaman this seem rather, well, wrong.  But I see my shaman as a worshiper of nature and the spirit world, somewhat like American Indians, and not of a particular deity.  *shrugs*  It works for me.<br><br>He started out with a full set of banded mail and has managed to replace some of it as hes gone along.  He has a few wisdom items and a few pieces of totemic armor.  I havent searched too hard in the bazaar because I wasnt sure what to shop for.  I like playing in groups, but I often find myself soloing.  It just depends on who is on and what mood Im in.  So I would like to be able to do both.  <br><br>Its interesting to hear that you are more of a caster than a tank.  Thats the way my druid started out.  He still uses his staff to beat monsters about the head and shoulders more than I think most druids do, but he really is a caster at this point.  Ive read some very interesting guides on how to solo a shaman to 60th level.  So I assumed they were played more like a tank than druids are.  But perhaps its more play style than just class abilities.  <br><br>Ill be searching in the bazaar for items as time goes by, but are there any popular items that many shaman tend to use?  Perhaps that might be a good angle to come at this problem from.  <br><br>&nbsp;<br><b>Namir Shadowstalker</b><br>Wood Elf Ranger, 49th Season<br><b>Calabar Silverthorn</b><br>Wood Elf Druid, 50th Season<br><b>Moonshadows</b><br><b>Seventh Hammer</b></td></tr>
