	   <tr><td colspan=2>Like I said, there are hard-core solo shamen who insist it's the only way to go.&nbsp;&nbsp;I am not one of them.  I think you'll progress much faster in a good group overall.<br><br>In my career, I've gone through phases, tank, DoTer, healer, and finally shaman :)  My philosophy is I will never be nearly as good a tank as a Warrior, or as good a Healer as a Cleric, but I can buff and debuff better than an Enchanter (overall), get mana back faster that most classes, and actually survive a few hits to boot.  At my level, the #1 thing people want is my SLOW ability.  It's a 70% slow at lvl 55, and it really makes a huge difference in battle. In my case, mana is king, so Wisdom, mana regen, and health regen are my top priorities.<br><br>For a soloer, I suppose AC is king.  Eventually, your gear will reflect your hunting style.  I have tried on accoasion to carry different kinds of equipment for different situations, but in the end I always end up just wearing what I use the most and banking or selling the rest.<br><br>Paw of Oppalla or Testament of Vaneer are probably the most common Shaman items at your level. I think at lvl 20 I was still in banded (but of course, that was back in the days when you had to walk uphill in the snow both ways)<br>&nbsp;<br>______________________________________<br><b>Dargadin, Barbarian Shaman of the 55th Season</b><br>Darg&nbsp;&nbsp; 41 Barb Warrior<br>Cyrius 21 Eru Wizard<br><b><br>Ayonae Ro Server</b></td></tr>
