	   <tr><td colspan=2>Smiter's Girdle is a belt and doesn't show any graphics. ;)<br><br>Green plaid you say eh? Take a look at my Magelo profile. The background pic shows what my Brown Chitin Leggings look like. Of course with Verant's logic, they're green plaid. Not brown. I got those for a sweet deal in Bazaar at around 800pp. Though I usually see them go for 1-2k. If you don't have the coin now, at least it gives you something to save for. They have fairly good stats too. I think they're a common drop off a named mob in FG so they's pretty common and you should see at least a couple in bazaar for sale. <br><br>In the meantime if you're looking for a cheap green plaid I do think I remember the Soiled Breechclot being a a green plaid too. They're common drop in Netherbian layer off one of the named mobs and are attainable by a group of low-mid twenties hunting there. Stats are only 8ac +3 wisdom, but it's good low end legs for a Shammy and at least for you it should be the right colour. ;)<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Tue Nov 26 16:53:19 2002</em><br>&nbsp;<br>Zaviax McCleo <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=235432" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=235432</a><br><br>Vykore Mainsnoir <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=234170" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=234170</a><br><br>Shadow of the Dragon<br>Tunare<br>(www.eqsod.com)</td></tr>
