	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Nov 8th 1:26 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[5.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Greetings.<br><br>Im looking for a little help / advice.<br><br>I have an SK for a main and havent played any other class too much at all.&nbsp;&nbsp;Translation?  I know an SK extremely well, but not any other class.<br><br>I recently have started bottin a Shaman friend from the same guild that I am in, but outside of the obvious things that they do, I have no clue what the hell I am doing.  =)  Im learning very quickly, but Im still totally wet behind the ears..<br><br>So, can you guys help me out a little?  <br><br>For instance:<br><br>1.  If I get agro, what is a SHM best defense?  Root?  Slow?  Heal?<br><br>2.  If adds come, what then becomes my best defense?  Should I aoe slow?  Should I heal the puller first?  Should I root adds?<br><br>3.  What are some really sweet spell combinations?<br><br>Any thoughts, including the questions above, woudl be greatly appreciated.<br><br>By the way, my SK and the SHM are both 61+ and geared very nicely if that helps in the analysis.<br><br>Thanks in advance,<br><br>Luna<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
