	   <tr><td colspan=2>He's right.<br>I wish people would stop posting stupid advice about why a shaman should have cha gear.<br>It's a waste of your time and money.<br>Cha only affects how much aggro an ench gets after a mob breaks mez.<br>Has nothing to do mob's resistance to slow, which is based solely on MR.<br>Invest your plat in some good HP/AC/Resist gear.<br>The higher you get in level, the more you realize that your mana pool is dependent on your life pool.<br><br>58 Shaman, Povar<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
