	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f104120445829044><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=9&mid=104120445829044>RE: Advice needed</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=9&mid=104120445829044#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=128738><span id= >NeonDistraction</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>12 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sun, Dec 29th 6:53 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I'm pretty sure the Malo line doesn't stack.<br><br>1. Not getting aggro - Usually I hit the mob with a malo at the beginning of the fight.&nbsp;&nbsp;It's very low aggro, and if it sticks, you probably won't have a problem landing slow.  Regardless, if the mob does resist, unless it has pretty high MR, I just cast Turgur's next.  Not doing so would be a waste of the cleric's mana, because around the 50's things hit hard, and your slow is 70% or more.<br><br>Sometimes this will still get you aggro, even though there's been some time for the tanks to taunt.  If I get aggro, I usually sit still long enough to get the mob taunted off me. (I was trained not to run away a long time ago by an enchanter friend, hehe.)  Running away will usually just create a chase, and it's much harder to taunt while your target is running away.  If slow landed and caused aggro, you usually have 5 or 10 seconds before you get hit anyway.  If not, I'll try to root and back off.<br><br>2. Healing - I have Chloroblast, but I don't usually keep it loaded unless I'm in a group without a cleric.  It doesn't heal as much as Superior, but has a faster casting time, making it a &quot;critical moment&quot; type heal.<br><br>If you're with a cleric, you probably won't have to worry about healing.  When clerics use their Complete Heal macro, you might throw a Superior Heal on if the target is still taking heavy damage.<br><br>And yea, start healing the cleric and especially the enchanter as soon as they start getting hit.  Enchanters can die before a heal goes off, so as soon as you see their life going down, heal them.<br><br>3 Spell lineup - Grouped and solo, my slots are pretty much the same, only a few trivials switched out.  In a group, my lineup is usually Superior Healing, Frost Strike (if there's an enchanter) / Bane of Nife (if there isn't), Malosi, Root (Paralyzing Earth, but yea), Chloroblast, Turgur's, Cannibalize III, group Regrowth.  Although I keep a DoT or DD up most of the time, I barely ever cast them, unless I have C3.<br><br>4. DoT's - If there's an enchanter, never DoT.  Ever.  DoT's make mesmerizing impossible, which is bad.  If something can't be mezzed because you dotted it, people will probably be angry with you.<br><br>5. Buffing - I believe that a fully buffed party is more effective than halfway.  Harnessing of Spirit is pretty mana-heavy, but the combined 50 str/dex is worth it in my opinion.  Strength probably only makes a marginal difference in damage later in the game, but dexterity will help people to proc their weapons more often.  (I was in a group once with two monks who had T-Staff's and 200+ dex; the amount of proccing was ridiculous lol.)  Give everyone agility; it helps dodge attacks.  I've had more than one enchanter comment on how my agility buff probably saved him from the angry mob.  Stamina, I usually only cast on the tanks and myself (so I have more health to eat).  And don't forget haste if there's no enchanters...your tanks won't.<br><br>Eh, I've said enough I think lol.  I hope that helps someone.<br><br>Xahra<br>56 Iksar Shaman<br>Luclin<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=143058" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=143058</a><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
