	   <tr><td colspan=2>&nbsp;&nbsp;On mobs that cant be rooted or snared best bet it to not get aggro. I know like Gullerback in Burning Woods cant be Turgurs slowed but diseease slowed only. If the mob is on you and not slowed let the cleric know and/or run circles around the group  to get a heal.<br>    In a small group, I still never use DD, maybe a Bane of Nife if there are other shaman/enchnaters to haste / slow.<br>  The message about mobs getting full damage from DoTs came out a month or 2 ago AFAIK. Mobs have always taken full damage while rooted or feared but not chasing you. Now it doesnt matter if they are feared, rooted or chasing you the DoT doed the same damage<br><br><br>56 Ogre Luminary on Luclin server--Chaotic Winds--Baron Aggrok<br><br><br><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
