	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Nov 8th 2:32 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.66]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>The Shaman can be a complex calss to play, especially is you didn't &quot;grow up&quot; a Shaman.<br>I'm not lvl 61, but I can give some insight.<br><br>BEFORE battle, make sure you've buffed everyone with the appropriate spell.&nbsp;&nbsp;CHA for the Enchanters, Agility for Everyone, STR and DEX and Regrowth for the Melees, etc.  It makes a BIG difference.<br><br>In my experience, the best thing you can do in battle is SLOW.  At your level, you can slow by 75%, thus cutting their damage output down to 1/4.   I haven't gotten AoE slow yet, but I'd worry that it would draw aggro toward me (yes, I am totally open to others' experience here).  I generally single slow the MoB the main is working on, and any MEZZED adds (if you are lucky enough to have an enchanter in the group).  If you have no mezzer, then slow each mob, but be ready to root and move.<br><br>If magic resistance is a problem, you can Malo (unresistable resistance debuff), or even better, if you have an enchanter to Tash, use Malosini.  It's resistable, but debuffs for more.<br><br>If there is no Cleric, Complete (75%) Heal the main tank when they get ot about half health.<br><br>When I get aggroed, I root and back up. I also try to use root to keep mobs away form people, but slowing is MUCH easier, and lasts longer.<br>Once the mobs are slowed, if you have mana to spare, you might toss some debuffs on the mobs, makes them easier to hit, etc.  These spells are underused IMHO.<br><br>Basically, a Shaman is so versatile, he can easily use up all his mana in two or three pulls if he does &quot;all of the above&quot;.  If mana conservation is important (as it almost always is) just focus on the slowing, you've got the BEST slow spell in the game.  Keep root up for self defense.  <br><br>Also, keep a Regeneration spell on you and do the &quot;Mana dance&quot; - Stand, Cannibalize, sit, repeat.  A hotkey is good for this:<br><br>/stand<br>/cast 1 (I keep Cannibalize in slot 1)<br>/pause 15 (or one more than the spell cast time)<br>/sit<br><br>Your tactics change depening on who's in the group with you.  If you've got a Druid, let him ROOT and DoT.  If you've got an Enchanter, let her Haste.  If you've got a Cleric, let him heal.  Try to balance mana useage among all the casters, so one of you isn't always the one who's OOM.<br>These are based on my experiences up to lvl 54.  Hope it's useful.<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Fri Nov  8 14:15:16 2002</em><br>&nbsp;<br>______________________________________<br><b>Dargadin, Barbarian Shaman of the 55th Season</b><br>Darg&nbsp;&nbsp; 41 Barb Warrior<br>Cyrius 21 Eru Wizard<br><b><br>Ayonae Ro Server</b></td></tr>
